[SN]TITLE[SN]
General Fiasco headline free Olympic torch concert

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Indie rock band General Fiasco are to be the headline act in a free concert to mark the arrival of the Olympic torch in Belfast.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The torch will arrive at City Hall on 6 June, after having toured Northern Ireland and visited Dublin.
The free concert, staged in the grounds of the City Hall from 6pm to 8pm, will include former Olympians, dance act Twist and Pulse, traditional fusion group Sontas and the City of Belfast School of Music junior choir.
Tickets are limited to four per person and are available at Belfast Welcome Centre.
